**OUTPUT FORMAT:**

```json
{
  "diagnosis": "string (confirmed or suspected diagnosis)",
  "staging": {
    "system": "string (staging system used, e.g., TNM, WHO grade)",
    "stage": "string (stage designation)",
    "components": {
      "description": "string (breakdown of staging components)"
    },
    "confidence": 0.0-1.0
  },
  "prognostic_factors": [
    {
{% if images and images|length > 0 %}
      "factor": "string (imaging feature)",
{% else %}
      "factor": "string (clinical/lab feature)",
{% endif %}
      "finding": "string (what was observed)",
      "implication": "favorable/unfavorable/neutral"
    }
  ],
{% if images and images|length > 0 %}
  "key_measurements": [
    {
      "measurement": "string (what was measured)",
      "value": "string (value with units)",
{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
      "image_index": 0,
{% endif %}
      "significance": "string (why this matters)"
    }
  ],
{% endif %}
  "treatment_implications": "string (how staging affects treatment decisions)",
  "follow_up_recommendations": ["list of recommended follow-up"],
  "limitations": "string (factors limiting staging accuracy)",
  "continue": true/false
}
```

**STAGING GUIDELINES:**

- Use established staging systems appropriate for the disease
{% if images and images|length > 0 %}
- Document all measurable disease
- Note features associated with prognosis (necrosis, enhancement patterns, etc.)
{% endif %}
- Consider searching medical literature for current staging criteria
- Be explicit about staging system version/year if applicable
{% if not images or images|length == 0 %}
- Note that staging based on clinical history alone may be limited
- Recommend imaging studies that would improve staging accuracy
{% endif %}

**COMMON STAGING SYSTEMS:**

Tumors: TNM staging, WHO grading (brain tumors), Rai/Binet (leukemia)
Brain lesions: Modified Rankin Scale, ASPECTS (stroke), Fazekas (white matter)
Liver: Child-Pugh, MELD, Barcelona Clinic (HCC)
Lung: TNM, mountain staging
